text: Code page 776 (also known as CP 776) is a code page used under DOS to write the Lithuanian language. It is a modification of Code page 770 to support the accented Lithuanian letters and phonetic symbols for Lithuanian. ==Character set== The following table shows code page 776. Each character is shown with its equivalent Unicode code point.
